notesStmt.note: Title of text from title abbreviations throughout, upper left verso and from colophon (f. 307v).
Title of commentary Lakṣmībharttuḥ prasarpatpadakamalabhuvaḥ from incipit (f. 1r).
307 leaves foliated 1-58, 60-308, upper left and lower right verso.
Colophon (main text): iti śrīmahābhārate śatasahasrāṃ saṃhitāyāṃ vaiyāśavabhāṃ udyogaparavasamāptamiti // śrīrastu // atraparvaṇyanivṛttāṃtā // (f. 307v).

Colophon (commentary): udyogaparvaṇi samāptam iti // vaśāvibhūṣitakarān navanīradābhāt pītāṃbarādaruṇabiṃbaphalādharoṣṭāt / pūrṇe[n]dusuṃramukhādaraviṃdanetrāt // kṛṣṇāt varaṃ kimapitatva maham na jāne // śubhaṃbhavatu // śrīrastu // (f. 308r)
Mistakes blacked out; some corrections in margins; verse markers indicated in orange throughout; vertical margins marked with quadruple orange line; has single wooden cover board.
Wooden board accompanies the manuscript for support.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Contains fifth book of the Mahābhārata, the Book of Effort, telling of the preparations for the epic war, beginning and end correspond with the critical edition (Mahābhārata, V.S. Sukthankar ed., Poona: Bhandarkar Oriental Research Institute, 1927-); contains an unidentified commentary running throughout, above and below the main text, beginning: Lakṣmībharttuḥ prasarpatpadakamalabhuvaḥ (f. 1v); missing both text and commentary of chapters 35 and 36 (missing f. 59).
